John Frayn Turner writes:
If a driver was to be knighted, it was Vernon Handley.
I knew him well during the decade from 1962 to 1982, when he was driving the Guildford Philharmonic.
Over the past 40 years, I’ve seen more than a hundred of his concerts, and I can honestly say that none of them ever disappointed me—and sometimes they even inspired me.
